modules.description: This module implements a flow-based communication layer with support for reading, writing, and managing the lifecycle of network connections. It handles `Cstruct.t` buffers for data transmission, offers `read`, `write`, and `writev` operations with error handling, and provides `shutdown` and `close` for connection termination. It is used to implement client-server protocols requiring reliable stream-based I/O, such as TLS or custom network services.

This module provides cryptographic operations for handshake protocols, including key generation, serialization, and validation of cryptographic primitives such as hash algorithms, AEAD ciphers, and elliptic curve points. It supports secure client-server authentication and key exchange by processing string-based cryptographic data to establish shared secrets for encrypted communication.
